      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@aldo.roman.nurena Very few differences.  GlassFish and JBoss both support the Java EE Full Profile, so they have support for legacy technologies like JAX-RPC and CORBA.  We didn&#39;t include these in the Java EE version of Tomcat, but all current technology is there like JAX-RS, JAX-WS, JMS, CDI, JPA, JSF, EJB, JTA, etc."
