      "body" : "Ummmm... As of last year, Tomcat was only 13 MB, GlassFish 53MB, and JBoss 127 MB.  I wouldn&#39;t consider those JavaEE servers (GlassFish and JBoss) hundreds of megs. If you are talking about WebLogic or WebSphere then we are talking about a GB. Info found at <a href=\"http://zeroturnaround.com/rebellabs/the-great-java-application-server-debate-with-tomcat-jboss-glassfish-jetty-and-liberty-profile/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">zeroturnaround.com/rebellabs/&hellip;</a>"
